Dali'sStringTheory {
; Two different visualizations of a segment of
; the Halley Nova I Mandelbrot set.  One
; relatively conventional view, the other an
; eliptical orbit trap,
; 
; As I look at this I see the cosmos and spiral
; galaxies with black holes at their centers.  The
; orbit traps took the shape distorted eye glass
; frames making me think of Salvador Dali.  It
; also makes me think of super strings, one of
; the more popular theories of the underlying
; structure of space time.
; 
; The conjunction of the Daliesque strings and
; conventional spirals is purely fortuitous.  It
; chaotic to the eye, yet it makes a sort of
; surealistic sense.
; 
; This was to be an entirely grey image.
; However, the lack of detail at the galaxy
; centers prompted me to add a touch of color
; by making some slight tweaks to the gradient
; in the lowest level.  I added psedo structure
; to the orbits by using a symetric gradient
; with a discontinuity.
; 
; Over all, this was a pleasing experiment.  Even
; working with an 800x600 image there was a
; lot of aliasing and lack of detail.  I was running
; on intuition and the hope that high resolution
; coupled with antialiasing would bring out
; hidden details.  The final image far surpassed
; my expectations.
;
fractal:
  title="Dali's String Theory" width=800 height=600
  author="Setemkia FallingTree" created="August 1, 2001" numlayers=4
layer:
  inalpha=0 outalpha=0 method=linear caption="New Layer 3" opacity=100
  visible=yes alpha=yes mergemode=luminance
mapping:
  center=-0.34495370370370368/0.704861111111111168 magn=32.7272727272727296
  angle=0
formula:
  filename="dmj.ufm" entry="dmj-HNovaIMandel" maxiter=50 percheck=off
  p_start=1/0 p_power=3/0 p_bailout=10000 p_fudge=yes
inside:
  filename="sft.ucl" entry="ElipseFirst" transfer=linear repeat=yes
  p_choose="Full Range" p_a=0.2 p_b=0.6 p_delta=0.05 p_center=-0.44/0.09682
  p_rotation=30
outside:
  filename="sft.ucl" entry="ElipseFirst" transfer=linear repeat=yes
  p_choose="Full Range" p_a=0.2 p_b=0.6 p_delta=0.05 p_center=-0.44/0.09682
  p_rotation=30
gradient:
  smooth=yes numnodes=2 index=0 color=0 index=399 color=16777215
alpha:
  smooth=yes numnodes=2 index=0 alpha=0 index=399 alpha=176
layer:
  inalpha=0 outalpha=0 method=linear caption="New Layer 2" opacity=100
  visible=yes alpha=yes mergemode=luminance
mapping:
  center=-0.34495370370370368/0.704861111111111168 magn=32.7272727272727296
  angle=0
formula:
  filename="dmj.ufm" entry="dmj-HNovaIMandel" maxiter=50 percheck=off
  p_start=1/0 p_power=3/0 p_bailout=10000 p_fudge=yes
inside:
  filename="sft.ucl" entry="ElipseFirst" transfer=linear repeat=yes
  p_choose="Full Range" p_a=0.2 p_b=0.6 p_delta=0.05 p_center=-0.44/0.09682
